      "writtenOn": "2026-01-28T12:08:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Both Ninja and Siso schedule validation actions as separate top level targets. That means if target A has validation B and C depends on A then C can run right after A is built and doesn\u0027t have to wait for B.\n\nEven if the build is interrupted after target A is built Ninja and Siso will do the right thing, i.e. build the validation target B.\n\nYou can find the logic here: \nhttps://github.com/ninja-build/ninja/blob/master/src/build.cc#L684-L694\nEven if a target is \u0027clean\u0027, i.e. doesn\u0027t need to be build, its validations are added as top level targets. \n\nI also verified this experimentally by:\n1. Building a target and its validation. \n2. Deleting only the validation output.\n3. Re-running the build and verifying that only the validation was run.\n\nHope this helps!",
      "parentUuid": "f1a889c6_b34629a4",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 2226,
        "startChar": 20,
        "endLine": 2226,
        "endChar": 58
      },
